<br>
In EQ, you couldn't continue if you didn't learn these things.  You either learned them, made a Druid or Necro and soloed...or you quit saying EQ sucks.  In DAoC, you don't NEED to learn these things.  Sure, it makes for great grouping, but when you don't NEED to group, why would you really want to learn how to?  I'll just go solo and make more exp and more money and kill what I want when I want.<br>
<br>
I love a good group.  I don't hate soloing, but it gets REALLY boring talking to myself (and you've all seen how much I can talk).  As I said before Quas...I'll follow you ex-EQers anywhere...its us that need to teach these ex-UOers and ex-ACers how an outstanding group works.  Either that, or we just group with each other, fly by them, and dominate their counterparts in the 2 other Realms when we hit RvR.<br>
<br>
My experiences on Percival (Midgard, Healer and Berserker), and Guinevere (Albion, Paladin and Cabalist) have shown that it very well may be the server we're on.  The RP servers do seem to have a better crop of players.  It may be coincidence...although even if it is, its nice knowing I won't run into anyone named Yourmom, Funkmeister, or Marcusthemagician. <p>-----------------------------------------<br>
<br>
For now, we are here<br>
Some day, we'll be there<br>
Until then, its wide open!<br>
<br>
--Wolfran Spiritwalker of White Wind<br>
